cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.LG

This paper deals with privacy-preserving recommendation systems for location-based services, which involves techniques from several sub-fields of computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on protecting users' location privacy. The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) techniques for processing and analyzing users' check-in data. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel objective function for learning user-POI and POI-POI relationships, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or social networks (cs.SI).
